					<common:class level="1">Food and renewable raw materials</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Oxidized starch is a modified starch obtained by treating food starch with sodium hypochlorite, adhering to good manufacturing practices (GMP). It is used in various industries, including paper, textiles, and food. The oxidation process endows it with unique properties such as shorter chain length, stable plasticity, improved whiteness, and reduced microbial counts. It has a low gelatinization temperature, high adhesion, and hydrogen bonding, which contribute to its durability. Oxidized starch (E1404) is a polysaccharide composed of glucose monomers linked in α 1,4 linkages.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氧化淀粉是一种变性淀粉，通过用次氯酸钠处理食品淀粉而获得，符合良好生产规范（GMP）。它可用于造纸、纺织和食品等多个行业。氧化过程使其具有独特的特性，如链长度较短、可塑性稳定、白度提高、微生物数量减少等。它的糊化温度低、粘附性高、氢键作用强，这些都有助于其耐久性。氧化淀粉（E1404）是一种多糖，由以 α 1,4 链节连接的葡萄糖单体组成。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>(C6H10O5)n</sumFormula>
